# ─── Boleto submission .gitignore ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Goal: ship the code + evidence, keep private idea/planning docs, heavy
# regenerable data, and model weights out of the public submission repo.

# --- Private idea / planning / pitch-prep docs (NOT for the submission) ------
boleto idea - 00.md
project creation plan.md
presentation-prep.md
# Kept on purpose (evidence judges should see): README.md, tradeoffs.md,
# results/FINAL-REPORT.md, results/WS-*.md. Delete a line above if you'd
# rather ship it, or add one below to hide more.

# --- Model weights: the LoRA adapters (1.2 GB, >100MB/file → GitHub rejects) -
# The LoRA negative-result STORY still ships via results/FINAL-REPORT.md and the
# small JSONs in evals/results/. The weights themselves are not needed to tell it.
evals/adapters/

# --- Heavy, regenerable synthetic data (261 MB; rebuilt by evals/generator.py)
evals/tickets_train/
evals/tickets_synthetic/

# --- Runtime artifacts (regenerated on demo/app run) ------------------------
demo_session/history.db
*.db

# --- Python ------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/
.pytest_cache/
.hypothesis/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/

# --- Virtualenvs -------------------------------------------------------------
.venv/
.venv-gemma/
venv/
env/

# --- OS / editor -------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# submission form copy and LinkedIn marketing assets (kept local, not in the repo)
DEVPOST.md
SETUP.md
assets/screenshots/linkedin/

# internal build reports, raw eval logs, dead scripts, baseline materials (kept local)
htr_harness.py
results/WS-*.md
!results/WS-F-*.md
evals/results/WS-*.md
evals/results/config_sweep_*
evals/results/eval_log.md
evals/results/eval_2026-07-19_*
evals/results/human_baseline/
evals/results/archive/
